Ad Text:
About the Role
We are looking for two Senior Associates to support monitoring and evaluation work across a major NSW grant and infrastructure program. You will review project proposals, assess expected outcomes and benefits, analyse data, and provide clear insights to help guide investment decisions.
This role is hands‑on and suited to someone who enjoys evaluation work, analysing information, preparing reports, and engaging with stakeholders.

What You’ll Do

Review infrastructure and community project proposals.
Analyse expected project outcomes, benefits, risks, and assumptions.
Conduct evaluations using qualitative and quantitative methods.
Prepare reports, summaries, dashboards, and insights for decision-makers.
Support ongoing monitoring across multiple funded programs.
Work with stakeholders to clarify project details and provide feedback.
Use analytical tools (including AI tools where helpful) to support evaluation work.
What We’re Looking For

5+ years experience in evaluation, impact assessment, analytics or similar.
Strong understanding of evaluation methods and data collection.
Ability to analyse information and translate it into simple, clear insights.
Confident communicator who can engage with different stakeholders.
Comfortable reviewing detailed project documents and giving feedback.
Nice to have:

Experience evaluating infrastructure, social, education, or health projects.
Experience with grant programs or Smarter Grants.
Understanding of NSW grants processes (not essential).
Why Apply?

Work on one of the biggest grant programs in NSW.
Exposure to high‑impact, high‑visibility projects.
Flexible working arrangements.
Strong chance of extension.
If you are interested in this role, please apply now or contact Andrew.murphy@Chandlermacleod.com



At Chandler Macleod, we are committed to fostering a diverse workforce where everyone is welcome. We encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, women, neurodiverse, people living with a disability and the LGBTIQA+ community.
You can read more about our commitment to diversity and inclusion at https://www.chandlermacleod.com/diversity-and-inclusion.

About the Role:
We are seeking an experienced Finance Transformation Manager to lead an organisation’s finance transformation agenda. This role will focus on implementing a new ERP and planning/reporting solutions, improving finance processes, and optimising the end-to-end finance operating model.

You will be responsible for delivering large-scale finance change initiatives, driving adoption of new ways of working, and ensuring alignment with organisational objectives. The role requires strong leadership, stakeholder management, and project governance skills, as well as a deep understanding of finance operations.


Key Responsibilities
Lead end-to-end finance transformation initiatives, including process improvement, planning, and reporting.
Drive user acceptance testing, training, cutover planning, data validation, and post-go-live optimisation.
Develop and execute change management plans to ensure business readiness and adoption.
Build strong relationships across executive and operational teams to influence and support transformation initiatives.
Establish and lead project governance forums, managing timelines, risks, budgets, and interdependencies.
Key Skills & Experience
Degree in Finance, Accounting, Business, Commerce or related discipline.
Professional accounting qualification (CPA, CA, CIMA or ACCA) highly regarded.
Proven experience delivering large-scale finance transformation programs.
Strong understanding of FP&A, Accounting, and Procurement processes.
Ability to lead cross-functional teams and influence senior stakeholders.
Experience managing complex change initiatives in dynamic environments.
Strong project management skills; certifications (e.g., PRINCE2, Agile) advantageous.
Excellent communication, problem-solving, and workshop facilitation skills.
This is a fantastic opportunity for a finance professional with a strong track record in transformation and change leadership to make a meaningful impact across the organisation.

Highly regarded not-for-profit organisation
WFH hybrid working options
$170K + super, and attractive NFP salary packaging 
The Organisation
Our client is a prominent national not-for-profit,  focused on expanding access to sustainable, low-cost residential solutions. Operating with a high-impact, mission-first ethos, they are committed to integrating advanced digital workflows to optimise service delivery and enhance the long-term well-being of the diverse populations they support.


The Role
The Enterprise Data & Platforms Manager is a pivotal leadership position responsible for the stability, governance, and continuous improvement of the organisation's core enterprise platforms. Reporting to the Head of Technology, you will act as the custodian of a sophisticated Microsoft D365 ecosystem (CRM and Business Central) and emerging Business Intelligence (Microsoft Fabric/Power BI) capabilities.


This role balances strategic oversight with hands-on technical delivery. You will lead a dedicated team to translate business needs into robust technical solutions, ensuring data is trusted, systems are secure, and insights drive impactful decision-making across the organisation.


Key Areas of Focus:
Strategic & Operational Leadership: Execute the platform roadmap, manage budgets, and define the BI and analytics strategy.
Technical Delivery & Governance: Provide hands-on leadership in design and configuration while overseeing disciplined change control and release management.
Data & Insights: Establish standards for data quality and semantic models, ensuring alignment between source systems and reporting outputs.
People Leadership: Mentor and uplift the capability of the Enterprise Platforms Team in systems analysis and data modelling.
Vendor & Stakeholder Management: Manage high-level vendor performance and partner with business leaders to drive platform adoption.
The Person
To be successful in this role, you will bring a blend of technical expertise and leadership maturity. You will have:
Demonstrated ability to lead technical teams and uplift capability in business analysis and documentation.
Proven experience in Dynamics 365 (CRM/Business Central) and the Power Platform.
Strong stakeholder management and influencing skills with experience in project management.
A strong governance mindset and understanding of structured change control, data privacy, and risk management.
A work history in the for-purpose sector and or/genuine passion for community-led outcomes and social impact.
The Offer
This is a permanent role offering the opportunity to shape the digital backbone of a major national NFP. Our client provides a flexible and supportive work environment, a competitive salary package of $170K + super, and attractive NFP salary packaging, along with the opportunity to lead a high-performing team in a mission-driven culture.


Are you ready to lead a digital transformation that makes a real-world difference? Then please make an application by clicking the 'Apply' tab below to submit your resume and cover letter in Word format. To confidentially discuss this role further, please feel free to call Lisa Pratt on (0493 632 441) or Barry Vienet on (0427 406 325) from Johnson Recruitment.


We are delighted to be managing another exclusive assignment created in partnership and trust with our client. Johnson Recruitment actively embraces diversity in the workforce through inclusive community representation of gender, culture, thought, and work arrangements.

About us: 
 
Billigence Pty Ltd is a specialist in the delivery of market-leading Business Intelligence and CRM solutions. Headquartered in Sydney, Australia and with offices in Prague, London, Frankfurt and Singapore our passion is data and our focus is the delivery of end-to-end solutions via a talented team of skilled professionals.  

We are partners with leading edge software platforms including Snowflake, dbt, Tableau, Alteryx, Collibra, and Salesforce.
  
What we are looking for:

We are seeking a Senior/Lead Data Engineer to join our growing Data Cloud Practice. You will work closely with our blue-chip banking clients.


Essential skills/experience required:

7-10+ years of experience across data engineering, cloud computing or data warehousing
Strong expertise in one or more of the following: Snowflake, Databricks, Redshift, Fabric, Cloudera or Teradata etc.
Willingness to up-skill in Snowflake if you do not have Snowflake experience
Strong data modelling experience & ETL processes
Strong expertise in SQL
Excellent communication skills, with the ability to collaborate across cross-functional teams and influence technical decisions.
Strong stake holder engagement skills/experience
Highly desirable:

Consulting experience
Design and architecture experience
Experience with dbt, Fivetran, Matillion
DevOps experience 
Experience with Python, Java, Scala nice to have.
Relevant certifications (SnowPro etc)
What’s in it for you?

Competitive salary + bonus
Opportunity to work on a variety of challenging projects
Be part of a global organisation.
Certifications provided
Learning & career growth opportunities.
Flexible, hybrid working model.
Company lunches & events.
Open, friendly team environment.
  
If this sounds like something you are interested in, please apply with your most up-to-date CV and we will be in touch!

Company description:



Capgemini is a global business and technology transformation partner, helping organisations to accelerate their dual transition to a digital and sustainable world, while creating tangible impact for enterprises and society. It is a responsible and diverse group of 340,000 team members in more than 50 countries. With its strong over 55-year heritage, Capgemini is trusted by its clients to unlock the value of technology to address the entire breadth of their business needs. It delivers end-to-end services and solutions leveraging strengths from strategy and design to engineering, all fuelled by its market leading capabilities in AI, cloud and data, combined with its deep industry expertise and partner ecosystem. The Group reported 2023 global revenues of 22.5 billion Euro.



Job description:

Let's talk about the Team

Cloud & Custom Applications (CCA) combine design and technology with modern delivery methodologies to deliver experience oriented, scalable, sustainable and secure enterprise solutions. We are tech savvy consultants on a journey to deliver innovation and expertise to our clients. Join a collaborative team that is solution focused and empower each other to be their best.
We are well known for our work on modern web applications; we are involved at all stages of the software delivery lifecycle from ideation through implementation to deployment. We're also strong on integrations, IoT, cloud migrations and app modernisation.

Let's Talk About The Role & Responsibilities

We're looking for a confident and experienced Senior Business Analyst to join our dynamic consultancy team in Wellington. This is a fantastic opportunity to work on large-scale, high-impact projects that shape business and technology outcomes for our clients.

As a Senior BA, you'll be the vital link between business needs and technical solutions. You'll bring clarity to complexity, working closely with stakeholders to define requirements, guide delivery, and ensure solutions are fit-for-purpose and future-ready.

Key Responsibilities
Act as the bridge between business stakeholders and technical teams, ensuring clear understanding and alignment of requirements.
Collaborate with project teams to break down deliverables into actionable activities and milestones.
Lead the analysis and definition of configuration specifications and business technology requirements.
Support the Solution Architect by clarifying business needs and contributing to solution design.
Engage with customers to co-design best practices and system functionality guidelines.
Maintain accurate and up-to-date documentation of technical and business information.
Support the full development lifecycle, from discovery through to delivery.
Take ownership of all business analysis activities required to fulfil project deliverables.
Build strong relationships with stakeholders, fostering trust and collaboration across diverse teams.
About You
Proven experience as a Senior Business Analyst in a consultancy or client-facing environment.
Hands on Scrum Master experience is required
Ideally some experience in the Retail Sector
Exceptional stakeholder engagement and communication skills.
Strong analytical thinking with the ability to translate business needs into technical requirements.
Comfortable working in fast-paced, complex project environments.
Experience supporting solution architecture and development lifecycles.
A proactive, collaborative approach with a focus on delivering value.


We offer:



Choosing Capgemini means choosing a company where you will be empowered to shape your career in the way you'd like, where you'll be supported and inspired by a collaborative community of colleagues around the world, and where you'll be able to reimagine what's possible. Join us and help the world's leading organizations unlock the value of technology and build a more sustainable, more inclusive world.

Leading ASX listed Services business requires an experienced Lean Six Sigma Black Belt to support a large-scale internal enterprise-wide transformation program on a 12 month fixed engagement.

This role is focused on embedding and optimising a new work order management operating model, driving sustainable improvements across efficiency, cost, customer experience, and risk.

You will work across a highly complex, regulated environment and partner closely with senior stakeholders to realise tangible, measurable benefits.

Daily Responsibilities will include;

Lead end-to-end Lean Six Sigma transformation initiatives across large, cross-functional environments
Embed and optimise new work order management processes aligned to an uplifted system
Drive continuous improvement and benefits realisation post-implementation
Reduce manual and low-value administrative activity through process and system redesign
Partner with senior leaders across multiple contracts and business units
Apply data-driven decision-making to measure outcomes and sustain improvements
To succeed in this role;

Lean Six Sigma Black Belt certification (essential)
Demonstrated experience delivering large, complex, cross-functional transformation programs
Strong stakeholder engagement and communication skills, including senior leadership
Experience working in regulated, infrastructure, or asset-intensive environments
Hands-on experience with work order management systems and operational process improvement
Strong analytical capability; experience using data, analytics, or AI is advantageous
A fantastic package is on offer for the successful candidate consisting on Base + Super.

Please call Patrick Egan @TalentWeb on 0407 261 441 or just hit the apply button below.

About us 
We are an award winning, national $16B public offer industry fund focused on the education and community sectors. Working for NGS Super means being part of something bigger and working to make a difference to our members and their financial future.  

Our people are key to our success, and as we expand, we’re committed to finding and retaining the right talent to take on the journey.  As well as a flexible and fun workplace, we offer competitive benefits including additional leave entitlements, personal & professional development and health & wellbeing programs. 

Click on the video below to learn more! 

The Role 
The Investment Performance and Compliance Manager plays a key role in delivering accurate, high quality investment performance reporting and ensuring the fund meets all mandate compliance requirements. You’ll take ownership of detailed data quality checks, oversee outputs from external service providers, and produce clear, reliable reporting that supports confident decision making.

You’ll also build strong working relationships with custodians, auditors, member communications teams, CRM specialists and digital teams. Reporting to the Head of Investment Operations, this role provides vital support across investment regulatory reporting, financial analytics and broader investment reporting needs for the fund.

What you’ll do

Complete and deliver weekly, monthly and quarterly investment performance reporting and insights, including quality assurance checks to ensure accuracy of the reporting and value-add for decision makers. 
Work closely with all members of the investment team to understand the investment strategies being implemented and ensure the investment performance is being measured consistently with the implementation strategy.
Monitor ongoing investment performance report from custodian and compare with the investment manager report.
Present investment performance reporting to internal teams to contribute to quality decision making.
Assist in the development and updating of performance reporting and insights to meet the needs of members, for publication on the website, in response to member queries and to support team members who engage with members.
Collect and validate data from various sources, including investment managers, custodians, and market data providers. Ensure data accuracy, completeness, and integrity for effective performance analysis to deliver reliable regulatory reporting of investment data and reporting to external ratings agencies.
Monitor and review mandate compliance reporting received from the custodian and directly from investment managers, reviewing any breaches and working closely with the Investments team on resolution.
Lead, develop and mentor a direct report to build capability and drive high performance.

About you 
A strategic thinker with an analytical mindset, you will bring the following key skills:

5+ years of practical experience in a performance analytics, fund accounting or corporate finance modelling role.
Experience in the full lifecycle of multi-sector investments, including listed securities as well as unlisted investments in private equity, infrastructure and/or real estate is highly desirable.
Advanced Microsoft Excel skills including VBA, PowerQuery, PowerPivot. 
High attention to detail and proven ability to deliver quality outcomes.
Demonstrated operational experience in the delivery of performance analytics.
Experience in a people leadership role including the development and mentoring of teams, or leading a project team.
Tertiary qualification in accounting, finance, mathematics, data science, statistics, advanced financial modelling or similar.

The following skills are nice to have but not essential

Prior experience in producing reports and insights using PowerBI or similar tools is highly desired.
Familiarity with machine learning tools, Chat GPT and similar AI tools is highly desired.
Hands-on experience using investment data platforms like FactSet, Bloomberg, eVestment, etc is desirable.
Operational experience in mandate compliance.

If you have a proven track record of success in Investment Performance and want to work for a truly member-focused super fund, we would love to hear from you.

We are a super fund that has an exceptional work culture, provides a diverse offering in developing our people and you can be a part of it while earning an attractive remuneration package! 

Interested and suitably qualified candidates should submit a copy of their updated CV. 

Please note that to be eligible for this role, you are required to have permanent Australian working rights and residency. 

We are an equal opportunity employer committed to creating a workplace that values diversity, equity, and respect for all individuals.

The Business Process Analyst will work with senior staff members to define
 end-to-end assessment lifecycle across the five faculties to understand opportunities and inefficiencies, that will translate into program requirements, tangible business analysis artefacts, solutions to achieve the desired outcomes and the benefits that will be realised.

The Business Process Analyst is responsible for understanding the business problem that needs to be solved, bridging the gap between business needs and technology solutions, analysing data, and providing strategic recommendations to improve processes and achieve business goals.

Key Responsibilities:
• End-to-end business functions analysis: Work with senior stakeholders to
understand, document and gain consensus of the assessment practices, and their strengths and weaknesses.
• Eliciting requirements: both functional and non-functional, creating use cases and user stories and other required project documentation
• Requirements Management: Work closely with various stakeholder groups to
effectively discover, define, validate, prioritise and continuously manage requirements that translate identified needs into solution outcomes which align with architectural principles and strategies.
• Process Improvement: Identify inefficiencies in workflows or systems and propose solutions to optimize business processes.
• Documentation: Create detailed documentation of requirements, workflows, and outcomes, including business process models to illustrate current and future states.
• Liaison Role: Act as a liaison between business stakeholders and technical teams,
ensuring smooth communication and understanding of project objectives.
• Workshop facilitation: Effectively facilitate sessions with diverse stakeholder groups, leveraging best-practice techniques and methodologies (such as design and systems thinking) to achieve desired objectives and outcomes.
• Collaboration: Collaborate with technical specialists, service management
stakeholders and relevant subject matter experts. Work with project team members to ensure processes are developed and coordinated with technological uplift to ensure process changes are implemented effectively.
• Reporting: Generate reports to communicate findings effectively to executive
audiences and other stakeholder groups.
• Benefits Management: Monitor and report on the benefits and performance of new processes and make recommendations for further improvements.
• Implementation Support: Participate in testing and validating new systems and processes to meet business requirements and ensure alignment with business goals.
• Training Support: Provide training and support to staff on new processes and tools.

Skills and Experience
• Minimum 5 years’ experience as a Lead Business Process Analyst or similar role
• Significant experience in end-to-end workflow analysis at a business process and technology level.
• Significant experience in business analysis techniques, with the demonstrated ability to collaborate with stakeholders and peers to conduct analysis, and rapidly and accurately elicit requirements.
• Exceptional analytical and problem-solving skills including the ability to conceptualise, establish and implement initiatives within a specified framework, including the ability to develop process mapping (as-is & to-be in BPMN), data and systems documentation in accordance with industry standards.
• Demonstrated experience supporting the successful delivery of high-impact and high value initiatives that lead to meaningful change and continuous improvement, with a proven ability to use initiative and self-drive to meet demanding deadlines.
• Excellent written communication skills, including the demonstrated ability to write clear and precise user and technical specifications, showcase presentations and reports.
• Strong interpersonal and communication skills to a senior executive level that cultivate and maintain productive, collaborative and outcomes-focused working relationships to anticipate and negotiate changes in client expectations and requirements.
• Ability to work independently and as part of a team.

Highly Desirable
• Higher Education sector or Government experience
• Experience in SaaS/COTS solution procurements and implementations

This position is based in Sydney.

An opportunity has become available for an experienced market risk professional to join a high-profile Treasury risk oversight team within a major financial services environment. This role sits within the second line of defence and plays a critical part in providing independent oversight across both traded and non-traded market risk exposures.

The Opportunity

You will support senior leadership in overseeing Treasury market risk exposures while delivering forward-looking analysis and governance across complex portfolios. This position offers significant exposure to Treasury strategy, regulatory frameworks and enterprise-wide risk management.

You’ll work closely with senior stakeholders and contribute directly to risk governance, regulatory compliance and strategic risk insight, making this a highly visible and influential position.

Key Responsibilities:

Market Risk Oversight

Provide independent oversight of traded and non-traded market risk exposures within Treasury
Analyse trades, positions and portfolio performance using risk metrics such as Value-at-Risk, sensitivity analysis and stress testing
Monitor structural and desk-level risk limits and identify emerging risk trends
Interpret drivers of Treasury performance, including impacts to P&L and risk profile
Maintain awareness of regulatory, market and industry developments
Governance & Regulatory Compliance

Contribute to the ongoing enhancement of market risk frameworks, policies and documentation
Identify and escalate governance or control gaps and support remediation initiatives
Review and challenge risk appetite settings and associated limit frameworks
Act as a subject matter expert across relevant Australian prudential standards including APS 116 and APS 117
Support change initiatives ensuring governance and control processes remain robust
Risk Analytics & Strategic Insight

Deliver meaningful risk analysis and reporting for senior leadership and risk committees
Provide insights into the impact of market risk exposures on earnings, capital and balance sheet outcomes
Collaborate with Treasury, analytics, modelling, stress testing and model risk teams
Build strong cross-functional stakeholder relationships across risk, finance, audit and Treasury business units

Requirements:

Excellent tertiary qualifications in a relevant field e.g. Finance, Commerce, Mathematics etc.
At least 5 years' Risk Management experience with exposure to Market Risk
Familiarity with regulatory standards APS 116, APS 117 (or both)
Strong understanding of Market Risk methodologies including VaR, sensitivities, and Stress Testing

For further information about these positions, please contact Olivia on 0409 356 856, email your CV to Olivia@BluefinResources.com.au or simply click APPLY.

Optus is an Australian telecommunications company, delivering more than 11 million services to our customers every day across mobile, broadband, and digital solutions.

The Portfolio Reporting Analyst sits within Optus' Billing and Credit function in Group Finance, providing analytical and reporting support to the Senior Portfolio Analyst and the wider Billing & Credit Performance Analytics team. The role contributes to secure customer onboarding, accurate billing, and effective credit and collections outcomes across all customer segments by enabling high quality insight, reliable reporting, and robust data foundations.

Working under the guidance of the Senior Portfolio Analyst, the role assists in translating complex data into clear insights that inform decision making across the end-to-end collections and recoveries lifecycle, including hardship. The position plays a key role in supporting performance analysis, reporting integrity, and stakeholder engagement, helping ensure senior leaders and stakeholders have the insights required to drive improvements in customer experience, operational efficiency, risk management, and financial outcomes.

What you'll be doing

Support the design, build, automation, and maintenance of dashboards, reports, and scorecards, ensuring alignment with best practice data visualisation standards and direction set by the Senior Portfolio Analyst.
Assist in the development and delivery of analysis and forecasting outputs by preparing data, identifying trends, and highlighting risks and opportunities for escalation and discussion.
Contribute to the translation of complex data into clear, consistent performance narratives to support portfolio level reporting and reviews.
Partner with Billing & Payments stakeholders to support performance discussions, respond to ad hoc analytical requests, and provide timely insights to inform business decisions.
Work closely with the Senior Portfolio Analyst to support portfolio deep dives, stakeholder packs, and executive ready reporting materials.
Collaborate with enterprise data and analytics teams to implement agreed reporting solutions in line with broader data strategy, standards, and best practice.
Support strong data accuracy and governance by maintaining reporting integrity, applying standardised definitions and methodologies, and assisting with the upkeep of data models and documentation.

What makes you perfect for the role?

University degree in business, finance, marketing, statistics, or a related field.
3+ years' experience supporting data analytics, integration, and visualisation initiatives within a complex environment.
Strong SQL capability, including complex querying and large-scale data manipulation to support analytical outcomes.
Experience using BI and analytics tools (e.g. Tableau, Cognos, Alteryx) and advanced Excel to produce reliable and repeatable reporting.
Exposure to complex data models, data quality considerations, and governance frameworks.
Strong analytical and communication skills, with the ability to present insights clearly and support engagement with senior stakeholders.

Optus is a place where we let you do you. We offer a range of benefits including:

Competitive remuneration and employee discounts. Make life easier (and more affordable) with $80 monthly credit and 25% off Optus products and unique shopping discounts with our retail partners.
Flexible working arrangements with opportunities to work three days in the office, two days remote or home.
Vibrant and collaborative office campus that includes cafes, convenience store, chill out zones, GP, post office, gym and on-site childcare centre.
Competitive leave policies, including additional 'Connected' days to focus on culture, family, health, community, or whatever's important to you.
We support growing families with inclusive, carer-neutral paid Parental Leave of up to 16 weeks.
Direct your own development and build future-ready skills with Optus U's industry-focused micro-credentials, developed with La Trobe and Macquarie Universities.
Build meaningful connections through employee-led networks and diversity initiatives including Culture Connect, Elevate Women, Disability Network and Express Yourself (LGBTQIA+).
Put your wellbeing first with free access to counselling and support services, 24/7 — in-person, by phone, SMS, or video.

At Optus, we are strengthened by others and that means valuing diversity and saying ‘yes' to embracing individual differences. We are committed to ensuring that our application process provides an equal employment opportunity to all job seekers, including individuals from diverse gender, cultural and linguistic backgrounds, individuals with a disability, individuals identifying as being part of the LGBTQIA+ community, individuals who may have served in the armed forces or who identify as Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander. We also want to do our best to make our recruitment process inclusive.

If you require any adjustments or accessibility support to participate fairly and equitably in the recruitment process, please email AccessibleRecruitment@optus.com.au or call 1800 309 170. We're here to help. When you contact us, please advise your preferred method of contact and we will be in touch within 48 hours.

For more information on Diversity, Inclusion & Belonging at Optus, please visit https://www.optus.com.au/about/inclusion-diversity.

Job Title: Anaplan Product Manager I Development Finance Team
Ad Text:
Company description:



At Stockland we are a community delivering outcomes that benefit the community at large. We work collaboratively and inclusively, building strong working relationships. Our portfolio is diverse and so are the opportunities for professional and career development. We are committed to providing our people with broad experiences to build a successful career.






Job description:



The Opportunity

We're looking for an experienced Anaplan Product Manager to join our Finance team within the Development division. This is a critical role responsible for designing, maintaining, and enhancing Anaplan models that support investment, forecasting, budgeting, and reporting across Stockland. You'll play a key role in shaping the Development Anaplan Roadmap and ensuring our financial planning solutions are scalable, accurate, and future-ready.

What You'll Do

In this role, you'll design, build, and optimise Anaplan models to support investment, planning, and reporting across Stockland. You'll collaborate with stakeholders to translate business needs into scalable solutions, manage the Development Anaplan Roadmap, and ensure data integrity through seamless integrations with enterprise systems. You'll create dashboards and insights for decision-making, mentor model builders, and champion best practices to enhance performance and usability, while providing training and support to empower end-users.

About You

You're passionate about leveraging technology to drive smarter financial decisions and thrive in a role where innovation and optimisation are key.

Experience & Skills That Count

· 5+ years in data analysis, financial modelling, or business intelligence.

· Proven experience delivering Anaplan solutions and integrations.

· Strong knowledge of financial processes (budgeting, forecasting, planning).

· Proficiency in SQL, Excel, and BI tools (PowerBI, Tableau).

· Project management experience across full lifecycle.

The Right Mindset

· Customer-centric and collaborative approach.

· Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.

· Ability to manage multiple priorities with attention to detail.

· Excellent communication skills to engage technical and non-technical stakeholders.

The Stockland Proposition

At Stockland, we create better places for everyone. We value Community, Accountability, Respect, and Excellence in everything we do. You'll join a team that embraces collaboration, adaptability, and enterprise leadership, with opportunities to grow your career in a supportive and future-focused environment.

Why Stockland

We offer a flexible and inclusive workplace, competitive benefits, and the chance to work on projects that shape communities across Australia. You'll be part of a company that invests in your development and champions innovation.

Ready to Apply?

If you're excited by the opportunity to make an impact and bring your expertise to a dynamic team, apply now and help us shape the future of financial planning at Stockland.

About us: 
 
Billigence Pty Ltd is a specialist in the delivery of market-leading Business Intelligence and CRM solutions. Headquartered in Sydney, Australia and with offices in Prague, London, Frankfurt and Singapore our passion is data and our focus is the delivery of end-to-end solutions via a talented team of skilled professionals.  

We are partners with leading edge software platforms including Tableau, Alteryx, Collibra, Snowflake and Salesforce.

What we are looking for:

A Senior Data Engineer with strong Snowflake experience to join our team & work on challenging banking projects. 

Initial 6 Month contract + extensions. Hybrid model, 2 days per week in the Sydney CBD office.

Essential skills/experience:

5+ Years data engineering experience 
Minimum 2+ years current commercial Snowflake experience
Solid Python experience 
Strong SQL experience
Excellent written & verbal communication skills are essential
Highly desirable: Snowflake certifications. 
Highly desirable: ML experience 

PLEASE NOTE: Only short listed candidates will be contacted.

Investment Analyst - Real Assets, Sydney-Based
 
The Opportunity
Following continued growth, a specialist real estate investment manager is appointing an Investment Analyst to support deal execution, underwriting, and investment analysis across a growing national pipeline.
 
The platform is active across industrial and logistics and data centres, with recent expansion into the Living sector through dedicated capability. The investment strategy is national in scope, with a primary focus on the eastern seaboard, where the majority of transaction activity occurs.
 
This is a hands-on role suited to someone who enjoys running hard at opportunities, building best-practice models and analysis, and operating in a lean, fast-paced environment where impact is visible and work is close to decision-makers.
 
Team & Working Style
The business operates with a lean leadership model and close collaboration between investment and development. The role works directly with senior leadership and experienced investment professionals across investment and development. Cultural fit is important, with an emphasis on collaboration, active participation, and confidence engaging across the team.
Key Responsibilities
 
Investment underwriting and modelling

Build and maintain detailed financial models for acquisitions and developments (DCF, IRR, waterfalls, sensitivity analysis, scenario modelling)
Support feasibility analysis for development-led opportunities, including cost, timing, and risk assessment
Assist in portfolio analytics and performance monitoring across existing and prospective investments
Due diligence and execution

Coordinate and support due diligence workstreams (commercial, technical, legal, tax, ESG, and planning)
Analyse leases, tenant covenants, cash flow, and capex requirements
Prepare investment committee materials, underwriting packs, and decision documentation aligned to institutional standards
Support transaction execution, working with advisers, counterparties, and internal stakeholders
Market and investment research

Conduct market, submarket, and asset-level research across industrial/logistics, data centres, and Living
Support investment strategy development and ongoing portfolio strategy work
Contribute to internal papers and insights to support decision-making
Stakeholder engagement

Work closely with internal investment and development teams to evaluate and progress live opportunities
Assist with communications and analysis for capital partners and key stakeholders as required
About You
The team is seeking a high-calibre Investment Analyst with strong technical capability, pace, and commercial judgement.
 
Experience

3-5 years' experience in investment banking or a comparable transaction-focused role where advanced modelling is core (real assets, M&A, infrastructure advisory, principal investing, or funds management)
Exposure to real estate is highly regarded, particularly across industrial/logistics, data centres, and development-led opportunities
Experience supporting transactions end-to-end (from evaluation through execution) will be well regarded
Technical capability

Advanced financial modelling and strong presentation skills
Ability to communicate complex analysis clearly and succinctly
High attention to detail and comfort operating with limited oversight in a lean environment
Personal attributes

Deals-driven and eager to take ownership
Commercially minded, proactive, and comfortable operating at pace
Strong work ethic and genuine interest in real estate investing and value creation
Motivated by working in a growing platform where performance and cultural contribution are visible
Why This Role
This is an opportunity to join a growing investment platform offering direct exposure to senior decision-makers and meaningful transaction responsibility, within a collaborative and performance-focused environment.

We are seeking an experienced and motivated professional to lead reporting, evaluation, and stakeholder engagement activities supporting complex reform initiatives. This role is critical in delivering high-quality, evidence-based reporting that demonstrates progress, impact, and accountability across reform programs.

About the Role You will apply a data- and evidence-led approach to evaluate reporting processes and contribute to broader reform evaluation activities. Working collaboratively across government, you will oversee the collection, analysis, and reporting of information to meet multiple departmental and governance requirements.

Key Responsibilities Evaluation and Reporting


Lead the evaluation of reporting processes and reform evaluation reports using robust data and evidence.


Develop and oversee frameworks, processes, and tools to gather, analyse, and report data across multiple reporting obligations.


Ensure compliance with governance and reporting frameworks, policies, and procedures.


Translate research findings into clear, meaningful insights to support reporting and engagement activities.


Stakeholder Engagement and Collaboration


Engage effectively with stakeholders across government to gather data and key inputs for reporting artefacts.


Build and maintain strong, trusted relationships that support collaboration and shared ownership of reform outcomes.


Coordinate contributions across agencies to ensure timely and accurate reporting.


Solutions-Focused Leadership


Foster a solutions-focused mindset within the team and among stakeholders to achieve required outcomes.


Provide expert advice and guidance to stakeholders and team members.


Contribute to a culture of innovation, continuous improvement, and accountability.


Communication and Performance


Prepare and present high-quality written materials, briefings, and presentations for senior executives and stakeholders.


Deliver concise, evidence-based reports to inform stakeholders on reform progress.


Communicate effectively with diverse audiences, ensuring transparency and alignment with strategic objectives.


Team Leadership and Development


Support the development of a high-performing and inclusive team culture.


Provide guidance and support to team members to ensure the successful delivery of reporting outputs.


About You You bring strong experience in reporting, evaluation, and stakeholder engagement within complex policy or reform environments. You are highly organised, collaborative, and confident communicating complex information clearly to senior audiences.

Ad Text:
Company description:



Insignia Financial Limited is an Australian financial services company which offers a range of products and services including financial advice, superannuation, investment management and trustee services



Job description:



We're seeking an experienced Senior Investment Analyst - Transition Management to play a critical role in managing complex, multi-asset class transitions within a multi-manager trust investment structure across Super and non-Super clients.

This role sits at the intersection of investment strategy, execution, and stakeholder management, partnering closely with MLC Asset Management to ensure asset management changes are implemented efficiently, cost-effectively, and with minimal risk, ultimately delivering better performance outcomes for members and clients.

How You'll Make an Impact

You'll be responsible for the end-to-end planning and execution of investment transitions, ensuring smooth delivery, strong governance, and best execution outcomes in a highly collaborative environment.

Key Responsibilities & Capabilities

Manage end-to-end asset transition projects across multi-asset, Super and non-Super unit trust structures, following approved investment changes
Plan and coordinate complex transitions including manager terminations and appointments, asset movements, legacy asset migration, and internal unit trust registry changes
Propose and implement transition strategies, considering member impact, unit registry transactions, liquidity, market impact, buy/sell spreads, tax (CGT, stamp duty), and implicit/explicit transaction costs
Appoint, coordinate, and monitor external transition managers and custodians, ensuring strong risk management, governance, and execution quality
Act as the central point of coordination across Investment, Fund Accounting & Operations, Custody, Product, and Legal to keep timelines, pipelines, and dependencies on track
Provide trading and execution advice (understanding trade execution and life cycle, without executing trades) and support cost analysis and financial modelling
Support new business activity including RFPs, pitches, and presentations, contributing analytical insight on asset allocation and investment structures
Build strong relationships with senior investment professionals through clear communication, proactive problem-solving, and a solutions-focused mindset

What you'll bring:

Extensive experience in financial services, wealth or asset management, with strong exposure to Unit Trust structures
Proven understanding of asset transition management and investment implementation within complex investment structures
Strong risk management mindset, able to question assumptions and assess downstream impacts
Solid knowledge of asset movements, execution strategies, liquidity, buy/sell spreads, and market impacts
Understanding of portfolio construction, asset allocation, and liquidity management, including tax considerations (e.g. CGT)
Highly organised and able to manage multiple concurrent, project-based transitions
Strong analytical and financial modelling skills, with advanced Excel capability
Autonomous, solutions-focused professional with strong stakeholder management and communication skills

This is a flat-structured team, but with exceptional exposure to senior investment professionals, complex investment decisions, and high-impact projects across the investment function. It's an ideal role for someone who wants breadth, depth, and visibility rather than a narrow operational pathway.

To Apply

Read more about why you should join our team https://www.insigniafinancial.com.au/careers/working-with-us/why-join-our-team.

Applicants will be required to provide evidence of their eligibility to work in Australia, and at a minimum be required to undertake police and basic credit checks as a condition of employment.

Company Description


Join the team redefining how the world experiences design.

Hey, g'day, mabuhay, kia ora, 你好, hallo, vítejte!
Thanks for stopping by. We know job hunting can be time-consuming, so let’s get straight to the point.

Where and how you can work

Our flagship campus is in Sydney, with additional spaces in Melbourne, Brisbane, Perth, and Adelaide. You have the flexibility to work from the office, home, or a mix of both—it’s your choice. We trust our Canvanauts to choose the balance that empowers them and their team to achieve their goals.

Job Description


What you’d be doing in this role

As Canva scales, change is part of our DNA. While your role will evolve over time, here’s a flavour of what you’ll be working on when you start:

Leading Product Analytics Engineering: Own and lead the Analytics Engineering function for the Product Org, with Product AEs reporting to you and the team expected to grow over time.

Driving Analytics Architecture of the Future: Define, own, and evolve Canva’s Product Analytics Engineering architecture, including modular data domains, semantic layers, metrics systems, and AI-ready foundations.

Elevating Analytics Engineering (AE) Craft: Set clear standards and best practices for analytics engineering across Product, and coach AEs across levels to consistently deliver high-quality, scalable data assets.

Partnering Across Product & Data: Work closely with Product Managers, Data Scientists, Engineers, and Platform teams to translate complex product needs into robust, reusable analytics solutions.

Balancing Strategy and Delivery: Combine long-term architectural thinking with pragmatic execution, ensuring AE effort is focused on the highest-impact Product initiatives.

Acting as a Technical Leader: Be the senior escalation point for complex analytics problems and represent Analytics Engineering perspectives in Product and Data leadership forums.

Enabling Product Decisions: Ensure analytics foundations enable product discovery, experimentation, launches, and long-term strategy, helping teams confidently understand user behaviour, product performance, and the impact of their decisions.

Hands-on Where It Matters Most: Get actively involved in complex or high-leverage analytics engineering work, while setting the technical direction for the team.

You're probably a match if…

You have extensive experience across Analytics Engineering, Data Engineering, or Software Engineering roles.

You’ve led and coached Analytics Engineering teams, including managing senior engineers and growing teams.

You’re deeply experienced with modern data platforms and tooling (e.g. SQL-based warehouses such as Snowflake, dbt-style transformations, orchestration, and semantic layers).

You have strong opinions (weakly held) — backed by experience — on data modelling, analytics architecture, and platform scalability and are eager to try new approaches.

You’re comfortable operating at the intersection of technical depth, people leadership, and strategy.

You thrive on collaboration and can communicate clearly with both highly technical partners and senior non-technical stakeholders.

You care deeply about data quality, reliability, performance, and cost efficiency.

About the team

Analytics Engineering sits within Canva’s broader Data ecosystem. The Product Analytics Engineering team partners closely with Product, Design and Engineering to ensure Canva’s product decisions are powered by trusted, timely, and scalable data foundations.

What's in it for you?

Achieving our crazy big goals motivates us to work hard—and we do—but you’ll experience lots of moments of magic, connectivity, and fun woven throughout life at Canva. Here’s a taste of what’s on offer:

Equity packages: We want our success to be yours too.

Inclusive parental leave policy: Supporting all parents and carers.

Annual Vibe & Thrive allowance: Supporting your wellbeing, social connection, office setup, and more.

Flexible leave options: Empowering you to recharge and take time for what matters most.

Other stuff to know

We value unique experiences and skills. If you don’t meet every requirement but feel passionate about this role, we’d still love to hear from you.

We make hiring decisions based on your experience, skills, and passion, as well as how you can enhance Canva and its culture. Let us know your pronouns and any reasonable adjustments you may need during the interview process.

Let’s make an impact together!

Job Description


Join the team redefining how the world experiences design.
Hey, g'day, mabuhay, kia ora, 你好, hallo, vítejte!

Where and how you can work
Our flagship campus is in Sydney. We also have a campus in Melbourne and co-working spaces in Brisbane, Perth and Adelaide. But you have choice in where and how you work, we trust our Canvanauts to choose the balance that empowers them and their team to achieve their goals.

What you'd be doing in this role
As Canva scales, change continues to be part of our DNA. But we like to think that's all part of the fun. So this will give you the flavour of the type of things you'll be working on when you start, but this will likely evolve.

At the moment, this role is focused on:

Leading the development of Infra Analytics data services, ensuring complex infrastructure insights are intuitive and accessible for stakeholders across Canva.

Architecting resilient, high-performance pipelines to orchestrate massive telemetry streams, maintaining the same scalability standards as our production systems.

Driving the technical strategy for data warehouse performance, ensuring efficient query execution and cost-effective storage for large-scale infra datasets.

Defining and promoting data modeling standards across the Infra Supergroup to ensure a unified and disciplined approach to data architecture.

Designing and maintaining a robust Infra semantic layer to guarantee a "single source of truth" for metrics and dimensions across all BI and analytical tools.

Partnering with cross-functional teams to lead the delivery of complex, high-impact projects from ideation to production.

Championing engineering best practices, with a focus on performance, scalability, reliability, and code quality.

You're probably a match if:

You have a proven track record of building scalable data solutions to solve complex, high-impact business challenges.

You’re fluent in advanced SQL and bring deep, hands-on experience in modern data modelling.

You’re proficient with Snowflake and AWS, and experienced with data transformation and orchestration tools (e.g. dbt, Airflow).

You are comfortable coding in Python.

You lead with an ownership mindset, communicate with clarity and influence, and thrive in collaborative, fast-moving environments.

A plus if you’re passionate about exploring emerging AI/ML opportunities.

About the team

The Infrastructure Analytics team serves as the stewards of Canva’s infrastructure analytics data, operating at the critical intersection of reliability, efficiency, and growth. Our mission is to transform raw infrastructure data into accessible, actionable insights that empower Canvanauts to make data-driven decisions regarding infrastructure optimization and scale. As the Center of Data Excellence for the Infra Supergroup, we don't just report on metrics but define the analytics landscape by managing the specialized data services, building scalable pipelines, and creating innovative analytical products. We act as strategic thought leaders and proactive problem-solvers, ensuring that data is a transformative force that drives Canva’s engineering innovation and continuous operational excellence.

What’s in it for you?
Achieving our crazy big goals motivates us to work hard — and we do — but you'll experience lots of moments of magic, connectivity and fun woven throughout life at Canva, too. We also offer a range of benefits to set you up for every success in and outside of work.

Here’s a taste of what’s on offer:
• Equity packages – we want our success to be yours too
• Inclusive parental leave policy that supports all parents & carers
• An annual Vibe & Thrive allowance to support your wellbeing, social connection, office setup & more
• Flexible leave options that empower you to be a force for good, take time to recharge and support you personally

Check out lifeatcanva.com for more info.

Other stuff to know

We celebrate all types of skills and backgrounds at Canva so even if you don't feel like your skills quite match what's listed above – we still want to hear from you!
